Hardware:
- Emotiv EPOC X     https://www.emotiv.com/epoc-x/
- Arduino UNO       https://www.arduino.cc/en/Main/arduinoBoardUno&gt;
- Digital WS2028b LEDstrips
- External power supply dependent on the amount of LEDs used
- Stereo amplifiers
- Optional: Audio interface (to relief some computational power from Ableton)

Software applications:
- Emotiv PRO        https://www.emotiv.com/emotivpro/
- OpenVibe acquisition server and scenario designer http://openvibe.inria.fr/downloads/
- Loop MIDI (or another virtual MIDI port app) http://www.tobias-erichsen.de/software/loopmidi.html
- Ableton Live 11 (Intro, Standard or Suite) https://www.ableton.com/en/shop/live/
- Asio4all (or another audio driver) https://asio4all.en.lo4d.com/windows
- Optional: software package accompanying the optionally used audio interface

Software 
- MINDYOURSELF_OpenVibe scenario \GITHUB LINK
- MINDYOURSELF_Arduino script \GITHUB LINK
- MINDYOURSELF_AbletonProject \GITHUB LINK
- MINDYOURSELF_SoundPackage \Soundcloud LINK (to be put in the same file location as the Ableton project/ or linked via missing files replacement (see below))
- MINDYOURSELF_PythonMain \GITHUB LINK

External additional information/tutorials:
- Manually linking sample files to Ableton            https://help.ableton.com/hc/en-us/articles/360000346779-How-to-find-and-replace-missing-media-files
- Setting up a virtual MIDI input port in Ableton     https://help.ableton.com/hc/en-us/articles/209774225-Setting-up-a-virtual-MIDI-bus
- Setting up Asio4All in Ableton                      https://help.ableton.com/hc/en-us/articles/115000204630-Setting-up-ASIO4ALL-Windows- 
                                                      (should be adapted if an external audio interface is used)
- Connecting the hardware of the LEDstrip to Arduino  https://learn.adafruit.com/adafruit-neopixel-uberguide/basic-connections
